race.comment: RUBY JUAN (4) jumped favourite and was too quick with an all-the-way win last start (22.11) at this track in a Grade 5 over 388m. Won at her only start from this box. Great chance again. PITMAN GO WELL (1) was big odds last time but gave a huge sight after a fast early split, grabbed late but holding on to a placing when a 4.5 lengths second (22.43) over 388m at this track. Well placed and gets his chance. NEW JACK (3) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.33) at this track behind Nova Reign in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to feature again. RED DIGGER (2) placed here at this trip last start - cannot be ignored.
